div.p:
In all cases where formal notification is not required the accused shall be
                    assisted in defence by counsel whenever reasonable and compatible with law;
                    otherwise he shall be assisted by an interpreter.

None of the military personnel of a prison camp, including interpreters, removed
                    from their positions on account of their attitude towards prisoners of war,
                    shall thereafter be employed in connection with prisoners of war.

list.item:
Captains and higher grades of the American army and marine corps;
                                lieutenants senior grade and officers of higher grades of the
                                American navy, line or staff corps.
